{
  "texts": [
    "The central server aggregates all received models to obtain the latest model M 𝑟 +1.",
    "Algorithm 1 summarizes the vanilla federated sequential recommendation procedures in pseudo-code.",
    "Algorithm 1 The pseudo-code for vanilla federated sequential recommendation.",
    "Input: global round 𝑅; learning rate 𝑙𝑟,... Output: well-trained sequential model M 𝑅 1: server initializes model M 0 2: for each round r =0,..., 𝑅 -1 do 3: sample a fraction of clients U 𝑟 from U 4: for 𝑢 𝑖 ∈ U 𝑟 in parallel do 5: // execute on client sides 6: M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖 ←ClientTrain(𝑢 𝑖, M 𝑟) 7: end for 8: // execute on central server 9: M 𝑟 +1 ← aggregate received client model parameters {M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖 } 𝑢 𝑖 ∈ U 𝑟 10: end for 11: function ClientTrain(𝑢 𝑖, M 𝑟) 12: M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖 ← update local model with recommendation objective L 𝑟𝑒𝑐 13:return M 𝑟 +1 𝑢 𝑖 14: end function Base Sequential Recommender SystemThe above FedSeqRec framework can be compatible with most current sequential recommendation models with reasonable sizes.",
    "In this paper, to demonstrate the generalization of our proposed FELLAS, we select the two most popular sequential recommendation models, GRU4Rec [20] and SASRec [22] as the experimental base models."
  ]
}